propDescriptions.action: The action to display. It renders after the message, at the end of the snackbar.
propDescriptions.anchorOrigin: The anchor of the Snackbar. On smaller screens, the component grows to occupy all the available width, the horizontal alignment is ignored.
propDescriptions.autoHideDuration: The number of milliseconds to wait before automatically calling the onClose function. onClose should then set the state of the open prop to hide the Snackbar. This behavior is disabled by default with the null value.
propDescriptions.classes: Override or extend the styles applied to the component. See CSS API below for more details.
propDescriptions.disableWindowBlurListener: If true, the autoHideDuration timer will expire even if the window is not focused.
propDescriptions.key: When displaying multiple consecutive Snackbars from a parent rendering a single <Snackbar/>, add the key prop to ensure independent treatment of each message. e.g. <Snackbar key={message} />, otherwise, the message may update-in-place and features such as autoHideDuration may be canceled.
propDescriptions.onClose:
Callback fired when the component requests to be closed. Typically onClose is used to set state in the parent component, which is used to control the Snackbar open prop. The reason parameter can optionally be used to control the response to onClose, for example ignoring clickaway.

Signature:
function(event: React.SyntheticEvent<any> | Event, reason: string) => void
event: The event source of the callback.
reason: Can be: "timeout" (autoHideDuration expired), "clickaway", or "escapeKeyDown".
propDescriptions.resumeHideDuration: The number of milliseconds to wait before dismissing after user interaction. If autoHideDuration prop isn't specified, it does nothing. If autoHideDuration prop is specified but resumeHideDuration isn't, we default to autoHideDuration / 2 ms.
propDescriptions.sx: The system prop that allows defining system overrides as well as additional CSS styles. See the `sx` page for more details.
propDescriptions.TransitionComponent: The component used for the transition. Follow this guide to learn more about the requirements for this component.
propDescriptions.transitionDuration: The duration for the transition, in milliseconds. You may specify a single timeout for all transitions, or individually with an object.
propDescriptions.TransitionProps: Props applied to the transition element. By default, the element is based on this Transition component.

root.description: Styles applied to the root element.
